  "text": "where the channel Reynold number is defined as Re c = U a H/ν. Clearly, in the developing flow region, the flow separation can easily occur with the smaller Ar. The criterion for distinguishing the flow separation in the developing flow region is fitted with the CFD data and plotted as a solid line in figure 9 , where its formula is described in equation [CITATION_1] . To obtain equation (9) to describe Re c as a function of Ar, we first employed the curve fitting subroutine, 'nonlinear least square' with the algorithm of 'trust-region-reflective' algorithm in Matlab with the data points from the CFD simulations. The result of this subroutine shows that a general rational function, of which both numerator and denominator have the same degree of 1, could lead to a good fitting. Therefore, we amended the rational function with an additional term of Re c − 25Ar as shown in equation (9), where the right Re c term would approach the fully developed parameter Re c (Ar =∞) when Re c increases to 25Ar. ",
